HTML Learning Syllabus
Basic Level- 1 week
1.      Introduction to HTML
·        What is HTML?
·        History and versions of HTML.
·        Basic structure of an HTML document.
·        HTML Editors.
2.      HTML Elements and Tags
·        Understanding elements and tags.
·        Common tags (e.g., <p>, <h1> to <h6>, <br>, <hr>).
3.      Attributes
·        Understanding attributes.
·        Common attributes (e.g., id, class, style).
4.      Formatting Text
·        Bold, italic, underline.
·        Superscript and subscript.
·        Font size and color.
5.      Creating Lists
·        Ordered lists (<ol>).
·        Unordered lists (<ul>).
·        Description lists (<dl>).
6.      Adding Links and Images
·        Creating hyperlinks (<a> tag).
·        Inserting images (<img> tag).
·        Relative vs absolute URLs.
7.      HTML Tables
·        Basic table structure (<table>, <tr>, <td>).
·        Table headers (<th>).
·        Rowspan and colspan attributes.
8.      Forms
·        Basic form structure (<form>).
·        Input types (text, radio, checkbox, etc.).
·        Labels, buttons, and fieldsets.
Intermediate Level- Practise based -1 week & parallel practise
9.      Advanced Text Formatting
·        Quotations (<blockquote>, <q>).
·        Code (<code>, <pre>).
10.  Advanced HTML Tables
·        Table captions (<caption>).
·        Column grouping (<col>, <colgroup>).
11.  Frames (Note: Frames are outdated and rarely used in modern web development)
·        Understanding frames and iframes.
·        Usage and drawbacks.
12.  HTML Semantics
·        Semantic elements (<header>, <footer>, <article>, <section>).
·        Importance for accessibility and SEO.
13.  HTML Forms in Depth
·        Advanced input types (date, color, range).
·        Form validation.
·        Form layout techniques.
14.  HTML5 Features
·        New semantic elements.
·        Audio and video integration. 
Advanced Level : Intro to JS so 1-2 weeks
 
16.  Responsive Design and Media Queries
·        Basics of responsive design.
·        Using media queries for device-specific layouts.
17.  HTML and JavaScript
·        Basic DOM manipulation.
·        Event handling.   
2:57
CSS Learning Syllabus
Basic Level: 3 - 4 days + practise
Introduction to CSS
Understanding CSS and its role in web design. 
Selectors and Properties
Basic selectors (e.g., class, id).
 Common properties (e.g., color, font-size).
Box Model
Understanding margin, border, padding, and content.
Layout Techniques
Introduction to layout models (e.g., block, inline).
 Basic positioning (relative, absolute).
Intermediate Level : 4 days  practice
Advanced Selectors
Combinators and pseudo-class selectors.
Responsive Design
Media queries.
Flexbox
Principles of Flexbox layout.
 Practical examples.

4. Grid Layout
Understanding CSS Grid.
 Building complex layouts.
Advanced Level: 2 days + practise
Animations and Transitions
Basic animations and keyframes.
 Transition effects.
